result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) and Operating w/ PAC (4th w/in 5 yrs). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (4th w/in 5 yrs) was dismissed by the court.

  • William B Thummel was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Defendant admitted to Veteran's Court.  6 days credit if revoked.

Ignition Interlock Device shall be installed prior to operating a motor vehicle.  The length of Ignition Interlock Device will begin when a valid driver's license or occupational license has been issued.  (Call Dept of Motor Vehicles with questions).

miscConds.notes: $2,023 - $225 (credit) = $1,798.    Plus supervision fees.    If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due. All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.
Any assessment and counseling as required and follow through and complete all required treatment.
Not to possess or consume any alcohol or illegal drugs.    Not to go on any premises where primary purpose is the sale of alcohol.    Not to possess any drug paraphernalia.
$31.60 represents Blood Draw Test fee.    $250 represents DNA surcharge.

timeConds.notes:
Commencement of sentence within 30 days.  May serve in Eau Claire County.
Pursuant to Hearing on 02/18/2016, 6 months Jail is stayed, pending completion of Veteran's Court.
Community Service as required by Veteran's Court.
